# Android Code Review Checklist

## Architecture
- [ ] ViewModel only calls use cases — no Retrofit/Repository direct access
- [ ] Repository impl extends `BaseRepository` and uses `safeApiCall`
- [ ] DTOs stay in `:data`, entities in `:domain`
- [ ] New bindings added to `RepositoryModule`

## State Management
- [ ] `StateFlow` for UI state, not mutable public properties
- [ ] Loading/success/error handled via `ResponseStates`
- [ ] Coroutines launched in `viewModelScope`, not GlobalScope

## Compose
- [ ] Stable parameters to composables; avoid unnecessary recomposition
- [ ] `remember` / `rememberSaveable` for expensive or stateful computations
- [ ] Design system components used (`common.compose.components`)
- [ ] No hardcoded colors/fonts — use `MaterialTheme` and project typography

## Navigation
- [ ] Routes defined in route objects, not inline strings
- [ ] Shared ViewModels scoped correctly (graph vs activity)
- [ ] Navigation args use `navArgument` with correct `NavType`

## Security & Performance
- [ ] No secrets in source code
- [ ] No blocking I/O on Main Thread
- [ ] Large lists use `LazyColumn`/`LazyRow` with keys
- [ ] Sensitive data not logged in production paths

## Strings & Resources
- [ ] User-facing strings in `strings.xml` via `getStringLocale()`
- [ ] No magic numbers — use named constants or theme dimensions
